on journal">Norrby, Lars J. (1991). "Why is mercury liquid? Or, why do relativistic effects not get into chemistry textbooks?". <i>Journal of Chemical Education</i>. <b>68</b> (2): 110. <a href="/wiki/Bibcode" title="Bibcode">Bibcode</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1991JChEd..68..110N">1991JChEd..68..110N</a>. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1021%2Fed068p110">10.1021/ed068p110</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARelativistic+quantum+chemistry&amp;rft.atitle=Why+is+mercury+liquid%3F+Or%2C+why+do+relativistic+effects+not+get+into+chemistry+textbooks%3F&amp;rft.aufirst=Lars+J.&amp;rft.aulast=Norrby&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Chemical+Education&amp;rft.pages=110&amp;rft.volume=68&amp;rft_id=info%3Abibcode%2F1991JChEd..68..110N&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1021%2Fed068p110&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Pitzer-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Pitzer_10-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation journal">Pitzer, Kenneth S. (1979). "Relativistic effects on chemical properties". <i>Accounts of Chemical Research</i>. <b>12</b> (8): 271. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1021%2Far50140a001">10.1021/ar50140a001</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARelativistic+quantum+chemistry&amp;rft.atitle=Relativistic+effects+on+chemical+properties&amp;rft.aufirst=Kenneth+S.&amp;rft.aulast=Pitzer&amp;rft.date=1979&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=8&amp;rft.jtitle=Accounts+of+Chemical+Research&amp;rft.page